Germany’s Budget Won’t Be Balanced by 2015, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   V i t s
-- 
2011-03-31T19:57:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/germany-s-budget-won-t-be-balanced-by-2015-handelsblatt-says.html
Germany ’s federal budget won’t be
in balance by 2015,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing unidentified
government officials.  German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  expects the
budget deficit to fall to 0.5 percent of gross domestic product
by 2015, the newspaper said. The budget deficit will amount to
2.5 percent of GDP this year and to 1.5 percent next and will
decline by 0.5 percentage points in 2013 and 2014, according to
the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Vits in Frankfurt at 
 cvits@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  